  "prompt": "How does Swift work?",
  "response": "Swift is a modern, multi-paradigm programming language developed by Apple for iOS, macOS, watchOS, and tvOS. Here's an overview of how Swift works:\n\n1. Compilation Process:\n```swift\n// Source Code (.swift) \u2192 Compiler \u2192 Intermediate Representation \u2192 Machine Code\n```\n\n2. Key Language Characteristics:\n- Statically typed\n- Type inference\n- Compiled language\n- Memory safe\n- Protocol-oriented\n- Object-oriented\n- Functional programming support\n\n3. Memory Management:\n- Automatic Reference Counting (ARC)\n- Manages memory automatically\n- Tracks and removes unused objects\n\n4. Basic Syntax Example:\n```swift\n// Variable declaration\nvar greeting = \"Hello, World!\"\n\n// Function definition\nfunc addNumbers(_ a: Int, _ b: Int) -> Int {\n    return a + b\n}\n\n// Class definition\nclass Person {\n    var name: String\n    \n    init(name: String) {\n        self.name = name\n    }\n}\n```\n\n5. Performance Features:\n- Compiled directly to machine code\n- Optimized for speed\n- Low-level performance similar to C\n- Safe memory management\n\n6. Type System:\n- Strong type checking\n- Type inference\n- Optional types\n- Generics support\n\n7. Runtime Characteristics:\n- Supports dynamic dispatch\n- Protocol extensions\n- Compile-time optimizations\n\n8. Interoperability:\n- Works with Objective-C\n- Can use existing frameworks\n- Bridgeable with C and Objective-C\n\n9. Compilation Stages:\n- Parsing\n- Type checking\n- Code generation\n- Optimization\n\n10. Memory Safety Features:\n- Prevents null pointer dereferencing\n- Bounds checking\n- Automatic memory management\n- Value vs. reference types\n\nSwift combines performance, safety, and modern programming concepts into a powerful, developer-friendly language.",
